\begin_inset Formula $\mu$
\end_inset

, and population standard deviation 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

) First recognize that these are a sample and we generally think of them
 to be representative of some population.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Second, the way that the two groups are different could be if the mean of
 group 1 is greater than the mean of the other.
 This is the most common difference to be interested in and we are usually
 interested in the difference between the mean responses.
 There is nothing to say that we couldn't look at the difference in variance,
 using the same method we'll cover next.
\end_layout

